content.detailedDescription:
Looking out of the window, my partner and i saw a glowing, moving object across the sky. it was definitely not an aeroplane. it came from one direction and was moving across the sky into another direction. then we saw another one, and another and another. the stream of objects appeared every few minutes, and they were not side by side, instead more like they were following one another. some were far off in the distance, others came nearer to our apartment (on the 4th floor). it was very apparent they were all coming from the same destination and heading to the same destination. the objects themselves, were like glowing balls when seen in the distance. the movement was not sproadic, instead the objects moved across the sky, some did go a bit faster at times, but overall the objects moved quite steady. sometimes a couple of them appeared to come closer to one another. 
interestingly, the same evening, it was a national fireworks night and so there were fireworks going off across the sky. please note, there was no way these moving objects were confused with fireworks, we have videos to demonstrate this, but it is interesting that such a lot of objects appeared the same night as when they could be partially camouflaged perhaps? as the evening progressed and the fireworks died down, so did the number of objects passing. at its most, we watched an object arrive and go every few minutes, it then slowed down to an object every 5-10 minutes (and then we went to bed). the objects did not suddenly disappear, instead they all continued to travel to a destination that we could not longer see from our apartment. one of the objects flew right above our apartment and the window and i saw it for a few seconds, it was like looking up at a bright, glowing circular object, about the size of a lorry. this close up allowed me to definitely see that this was a ufo. also when taking photos, we could see through the lens, a circles of lights like windows, but i could not see this with the naked eye, and the photos did not show this (cheap mobile camera phone, no professional camera). this is not the first time we have seen ufo's in this same area, it seems there is activity in this area. i took about 80 photos in total, and about 20 videos, i compiled some of the videos together and zoomed in and slowed down some of the video. on some of the photos, i zoomed in.
content.summary: Over a few hours, 40 plus same craft came from the same direction, heading towards the same direction, all on evening when country had national fireworks night

content.detailedDescription:
I was on the cell phone speaking to a friend of mine at approx. 2:15-2:30am. we had been talking for over an hour and i had been smoking cigs, walking the porch and enjoying the clear night and nice weather.  i had sat down on the steps to continue the conversation and approx. 10 minutes i noticed first off - the fact i could not see any stars in an area.  the fact i could see some stars but in an area i could not see any - it did not seem right at all, i did not think at that moment i was looking at anything.  i kept looking and then realized when the end of this 'area' was then allowing me to see the stars.  at that moment i realized something was in front of me and it was large, i could then see the size due to the area i could not see.  i then was very close to the craft and see details of it.  it was black with not shiny but not dull surface.  it was approx. 3 stories tall, approx. 300 ft long, approx. 75 ft wide. it traveled from north to south.  i saw the entire west side of the craft.  i did not the front at all.  i could see part of the back end, but limited due to the dark color craft at night time.  i did not notice the bottom of the craft until it was a light blue/white or white/light blue light, it was a softer than normal led light.  this light appeared to run the width of the craft.  the height of the bottom of the craft to the ground was approx. 15 ft above the trees.  i did notice that the trees did not move.  

when i realized there was a large craft not very far from me, i did not move.  i knew that this was not anything i had seen, heard of or thought should be flying!  it did not make any sense that it could be moving.  it looked heavy and not a way to stay in the air, no wings, etc. with no sound at all, it did bother me that i was in possible danger when i saw the light.  

it was only traveling approx. 2 mph and continued south until i could not see it any longer.  i did not want to follow the craft down the road, i didn't want the craft to notice me and i figured it could leave fast if need be.  

i can show you the exact spot i was sitting, where the craft was - i will never forget that.
content.summary: Black very large retangle with white/blueish light on bottom

content.detailedDescription: I live in a big three story house that sits on a ridge overlooking forrest crossing golf course here in franklin. the back side of my house faces directly west, so there are windows all across the back side of my house for the view and sunset. it was dark out already, time was about 6:22pm cst, and it had just snowed the two days prior. tonight was a nice clear night though, because all of the weather had moved past us. i was walking upstairs to my 3rd floor living room and glanced out the back window and saw two very bright orange colored orbs ascending parallel to one another(very low to the ground), and i knew immediately it was out of the ordinary. so i rushed out to my 3rd floor balcony and started filming them with my iphone as they continued to silently ascend. in the video, you can hear the kids outside on the golf course(in the dark), out playing/sledding in the snow. as the objects ascended, it looked like two circular/ball-like orbs that were spinning and changing shape and color as they went up in the air parallel to one another. they got up to about 45 degrees from the horizon, and the orb on the left started to fizzle and finally dematerialized after spinning very fast. the orb on the right followed suit and did the same about 10 seconds later. there was no sound..No blinking 'safety lights' that an aircraft would have...And i never saw them again that night or since then. when i downloaded the video onto my computer and looked at it frame by frame, you can see a multitude of various colored dots/lights surrounding the air around each orb. as each orb spins in place, it would change color from white to yellow to orange to pink/red and then back again to white and start the process over again. it seems they had some sort of "field" around them too. this field can be seen in the video frame by frame. the field looks like a lot of smaller orbs surrounding the large two orbs, and the colors of the 'field' were violet, white, red, yellow(i didn't notice this 'field' in person, only when i watched the video later). i've never seen anything like this before, and i watch planes come in and leave all the time, heading to our airport here in nashville. these were not planes, and were not drones...They were something else entirely.
content.summary: Two color changing orbs flying parallel with no noise, ascending slowly and disappearing.

content.detailedDescription: While camping as a teen in the yard over the summer, i was drawn to one cluster of stars that used to appear between two power lines that ran behind our property. every night i'd see these same six or so stars in the same area again and again, week after week between tow of the wires. sometimes the group would appear a little lower or a little above these two wires that bracketed them but i always sat in the same place to observe them so i knew they were not normal stars, after all, stars do not move that much distance in just one night. i got the feeling that it wasn't just me watching these stars, but i felt that they were observing me also.  i finally decided to think "i know you're watching me." so for several nights i would say the same thing in my head again. a few nights later i decided to say, "you know i'm here watching, don't  you?" the star on the far right glowed slightly brighter then it vanished. i watched the spot between the wires again and again over the next few nights but it was still gone, but the others remained, then the star reappeared in the same place once again. they were there for a few days more but then just vanished from the spot in the sky that they occupied for weeks. i never saw them again, until later that summer, when they were back one night only, i looked at them for a few minutes and then crawled into my tent for the night. a few moments passed and the yard lit up with an intensely bright yellow golden light . i lifted the edge of the tent to see the yard. the light was everywhere but no shadows were being cast. it seemed to flare up birghter if that was even possible, and just that quick, the light was gone. that was the first time i had seen something out of the ordinary like that but not the last.
content.summary: Was drawn to "stars" at one point in sky night after night for several weeks, looked one night, said, "you know im here watching," and one of the stars on the end disappeared.  need to talk to someone, theres a lot more events.

i thought about using my cellphone to record the event but i know that my resolution would not be high enough to catch these tiny dots in the sky so did not attempt to record by picture or video, i do also apologize to some reading for my likely many typos as i am not strong in my grammer skills.

content.detailedDescription:
After enjoying a beautiful clear day riding my motorcycle i decided to stop off at a riverside park to wind down for the evening. perfect evening, the skies were crystal clear, nearly no wind and the temperatures were considered warm (50-60's) for mid-march. i could hear the hum of the industrial area around me, the sound of cars, birds and other life of the river. it was an ideal evening to just sit and relax.
sitting on a bench on the banks of the river, a weird calm and quiet came over the area. all of the animals had silenced as if a switch was turned on. it grabbed my attention. the whole time, i happened to be stretched out on the bench looking up at the clear night sky looking for satellites, ufos and watching the bats gobble up insects, so my eyes were somewhat trained at looking for distant/rapid objects. 
at approximately 7:05pm i spotted a black almost translucent or cloaked pyramid object with four faint red/orange pods at each corner. at first i thought i had finally spotted a tr-3b craft but noted to myself this object had four pods on corners, not three with a large dome in the center. (note- since my last ufo spotting and submission to mufon, i have been very curious about ufo's and have been doing quite a bit of research on a serious hobby basis)
back to the first craft...
first craft seemed to be 5 sided, much like the indian vimana as described as a large flying pyramid. made absolutely no noise. size at altitude was estimated 300-400 feet wide side to side. was traveling at almost perfect south to north trajectory at an incredible steady speed. my estimates of altitude was probably between 5000-10000 feet. speed, estimate based on first sight of object at almost straight up to horizon was roughly four seconds. 3000+ mph at least. no sound, but obviously a solid object traveling very fast.
object seemed to be cloaked but was slightly visible with clear definition of structure, bottom was reflecting or absorbing the light pollution given off by the city. the night sky and the position of the setting sun left the sky a very slight blue tint. it was a perfect backdrop to see a black object as i was spotting bats swooping around the park.
the second and third objects were identical to each other. very large chevron or boomerang objects two minutes after the first one. these objects seem to be on a pursuit trajectory toward the last known position to the first one. nearly two minutes after i spotted the pyramid craft. i know this because after the first sighting i pulled my phone out to check time and make mental note of time and my location.
first (second of three) craft appeared to be on a elliptical left hand turn towards the first object (from sw to east then north). the second chevron seemed to have come from the east-south east and going north north west to intercept or meet up with the first chevron craft. no sound at all.
descriptions match the 600 feet or larger boomerang/flying wing craft that can be found all over the internet. five red/orange pods or antigravity engines on the bottom of the two crafts. same translucent appearance, but these craft had definite crisp front leading edges. altitude was same as original craft 5000-10000 feet, but were traveling at a much greater speed. both seemed to be chasing, pursuing, or patrolling the area. definitely on course with the first one. it was impressive witnessing such large silent objects traveling at those speeds and making the rapid turns they performed. the red/orange glows on the objects were the defining tell to spot these craft. much like very, very, very dim led lights flickering.
at first i doubted what i saw, then my logical mechanic/engineer mind kicked in and i just sat there and replayed the sighting in my mind. 
this is not the first time i've seen ufos, lights or unexplainable large objects and i know it probably wont be the last. 
most people don't fix or train their eyes and just zone out to the open sky. i liken seeing these objects as training your eyes to see those hidden 3-d pictures that were popular in the 90's. much like seeing past and into the dark.
very impressive display not seen every day. i would like to sit down with a mufon investigator and possibly get to the bottom of this most recent sighting.

content.detailedDescription:
Note: the attached pic makes object appear smooth-edged. that's only because of the distance away from the object when i was able to take the photo. 
i was taking the trash out to the curb at about 8:30. walking back to the house a bright orangish moving object caught my eye at about my 2 o'clock. i was initially very surprised because i couldn't figure out what it may have been and my location in the next couple of seconds (at the west side of my house) prevented any further view. i went in the house and told my wife that i had seen something very unusual then decided to go into the backyard to see if may have been a helicopter. but instinctively i new better. almost as soon as i went into the backyard another identical object entered my vision off to my left (west)! i admit that i was completely stupefied and found myself unable to make any sense out of what i was seeing. the object continued in a straight line overhead and off to my right (east). note: the night sky was partly cloudy (low patches of white)  to the west but in many places beautifully clear with stars visible. this was both to the west and overhead and to some extent eastward. further east, the clouds appeared both thicker and lower. the object coming out of the west was well below the few clouds that existed there and, overhead, it passed thru clear sky. as it continued eastward it actually disappeared in the lower elevation of the cloud cover. i keep saying "it"; however, i saw a total of four of these objects. they were identical in appearance, at the same elevation, of the same color and other characteristics and, mostly notably: made no sound whatsoever. i'm guessing here but i would put their elevation at about 1500-2000 feet. pure guess! wa h object would pass out of sight in the east for perhaps a 30 secs to 1min before the next one would come out of the west. it my pic is of the fourth one as i simply didn't think to take my phone with me when i went in the backyard and was so mesmerized that i didn't think to get until the fourth object was on its was. i managed to get 3 pics of that one object but already to my east! i was so dumbfounded when the next one came along that, having selected video on my phone, i forgot to hit the record button. there are a few characteristics about the objects i haven't been able to get into here because it would be too difficult to describe with the written word. once again, the pics are of the same object as it is already moving away from me. what i would really like to know is if this is a new military aircraft. the silence of the objects as the flew across the sky was very troubling!
content.summary: Circular or ball-like. bright orange/red. outer edge ring somewhat transparent. edges not smooth.

content.detailedDescription: I was waiting in the parking lot at the rlds temple when i observed an object moving in slowly from the ne, then it stopped and hovered in the same position just ne of the temple for approximately 20 minutes. it had a reflective silver and black surface and lights in a triangular shape, but when it moved i could see that it had some sort of appendages like wings on the sides. it was difficult to tell if it was a triangle shape or something else, because it was so dark outside. the object appeared to be watching something, them it took off slowly, then sped up quickly after that and moved out of sight behind the tree line and buildings.  it was at about 80 - 100' from the ground and appeared to be the size of a volkswagon. there was absolutely no sound, and that is what perplexed me. if it had been a helicopter or even a drone, i would have expected to hear a sound as close as it was. i think i was only 100' or less away from it. there were no other people around at the time.
content.summary: Hovering object with red lights over rlds temple
